HEADWORD: Cribration
<hw>Cri*bra"tion</hw> <pr>(kr?-br?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>cribration</ets>, fr. L. <ets>cribrare</ets> to sift. See
<er>Cribble</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Pharmacy)</fld> <def>The
act or process of separating the finer parts of drugs from the coarser
by sifting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cribriform</ent>⟦br⟧
